        "type": "text",
        "content": "TESTING VARIABLES"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "In the normal course of dialog development, variables are set and"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "displayed in panels. To display or alter a variable's content,"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "select Dialog Test Option 3."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The table presented contains all variables visible to the dialog"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "test session from function, shared, global, and profile pools."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Each row in the table contains a line command area, the variable"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "name, the pool indicator (F,S,G, or P), and the variable value."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "With Variable Test you can:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "\u0007  Insert new variables using the 'I' line command."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "\u0007  Delete variables using the 'D' line command."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "\u0007  Copy variables using the 'C' line command."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
